summary: This document is an electronic communication from the FBI regarding the late submission of recordings related to the case involving Alfredo Rodriguez. It details the consensually monitored phone calls between Rodriguez and a complaining witness, as well as surveillance footage from an incident on November 3, 2009. The delay in submission was attributed to the case agent's temporary duty assignment in Afghanistan.

keyFacts: The document discusses the late submission of recordings to ELSUR.
Consensually monitored phone calls between Alfredo Rodriguez and a complaining witness were included.
The delay in submission was due to the case agent's temporary duty assignment to Afghanistan.
